7 An Act relating to students; amending Section 1,
Chapter 297, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
8 6-401), which relates to electronic or digital
communications between students and school personnel;
9 providing for inclusion of alternate adult in
communications with certain students; providing
10 exception; updating statutory reference; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 AUTHOR: Add the following House Coauthor: Moore
14 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the title, enacting clause, and entire bill
and insert:
15
16
17 "An Act relating to students; amending Section 1,
Chapter 297, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
18 6-401), which relates to electronic or digital
communications between students and school personnel;
19 defining alternate adult; requiring written
verification; requiring notice of certain changes in
20 student circumstances; defining student; providing
for inclusion of alternate adult in certain
21 communications; and updating statutory reference.
22
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 799 Page 1
1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 297, O.S.L.
2 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 6-401), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 6-401. A. As used in this section:
5 1. "Alternate adult" means a case manager or designated
6 employee of a homeless shelter, transitional living program, or a
7 continuum of care lead agency assigned to a student who has been
8 verified by the alternate adult as provided in subparagraph a of
9 this paragraph to be a homeless child or youth as defined in Section
10 600 of Title 10 of the Oklahoma Statutes without objection from the
11 student's parent or legal guardian.
12 a. Before the school shall include an alternate adult in
13 any electronic or digital communications, the
14 alternate adult shall:
15 (1) send a letter by return receipt mail to the last-
16 known address of the parent or legal guardian of
17 the student informing the parent or legal
18 guardian that the student may be designated as a
19 homeless child or youth and that an alternate
20 adult may be assigned to the student in school-
21 related communications if no response or
22 objection is received,
23
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 799 Page 2
1 (2) allow a period of no less than fifteen (15)
2 business days for the parent or legal guardian to
3 respond or object to such designation, and
4 (3) file written verification with the school that no
5 objection was received, reasonable efforts to
6 locate or contact the parent or legal guardian
7 have been unsuccessful, and that the student
8 shall be designated as a homeless child or youth
9 and the alternate adult shall be included in
10 student-related communications.
11 b. The alternate adult shall promptly notify the school
12 if the alternate adult is no longer assigned to the
13 student, the student no longer meets the definition of
14 a homeless child or youth, a parent or legal guardian
15 objects to the student's designation, or any other
16 significant change in the student's circumstances as a
17 homeless child or youth;
18 2. "Electronic or digital communication" includes, but is not
19 limited to, emails, text messages, instant messages, direct
20 messages, social media messages, messages sent through software
21 applications, and any other electronic or digital means of
22 communication; and
23
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 799 Page 3
1 2. 3. "School personnel" means teachers, coaches,
2 administrators, school bus drivers, or any other persons employed
3 full-time or part-time by a public school or charter school; and
4 4. "Student" means a person enrolled in a public school or
5 charter school in this state receiving primary or secondary
6 education to obtain a standard high school diploma or high school
7 equivalency diploma. Student does not mean a person who holds a
8 standard high school diploma or high school equivalency diploma.
9 B. School personnel engaging in electronic or digital
10 communication with an individual student shall include the student's
11 parent or, legal guardian, or alternate adult in any electronic or
12 digital communication, unless such communication is on a school-
13 approved platform and related to school and academic communications.
14 C. Exceptions to the requirement in subsection B of this
15 section may be made in case of an emergency, subject to subsequent
16 notification to the parent or, legal guardian, or alternate adult.
17 D. School personnel shall make reasonable efforts to use
18 school-approved platforms, systems, or applications that allow
19 automatic inclusion of parents or, legal guardians, or alternate
20 adults in communications with students.
21 D. E. Schools shall provide training, developed by the State
22 Department of Education, for school personnel on the student
23 communication requirements of this section.
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 799 Page 4
1 E. F. Any school personnel who is reported to be in violation
2 of subsection B of this section shall be put on administrative leave
3 while the school district investigates the incident and notifies the
4 board of education. If the investigation finds that no misconduct
5 occurred, the school personnel shall be reinstated and the incident
6 shall be noted in the school personnel's employee file. If the
7 investigation finds misconduct occurred, the school personnel shall
8 be disciplined according to the school district board of education's
9 policy, up to and including termination of employment, and the
10 incident shall be reported to law enforcement pursuant to Section
11 1210.163 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title."
